The National Security Council (NSC) and the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) have received a preliminary briefing from the Council of Inspectors General on Integrity and Efficiency (CIGIE) regarding their evaluation of the operations of the Special Inspector General for Afghan Reconstruction. The review was conducted at the request of the NSC, in coordination with the Department of Defense and the Department of State. The goal of the review is to minimize waste, fraud, and abuse in reconstruction efforts in Afghanistan. The NSC appreciates the expertise and independence of CIGIE and looks forward to receiving their final report in a few weeks.